content:
Sales reps, group admins, or insurance brokers can use the spreadsheet Census Uploader to upload a group benefits census file to Vlocity. In addition to member and dependent data (name, birthdate), this file can also include product enrollment information.

The Uploader has a mapper feature which is used to map fields in the spreadsheet to Vlocity fields as needed.

Vlocity provides a way for you to auto number your censuses so you can have a unique number for each census. If you want to get fancy, you can create custom formulas to auto-generate a census number encoded with special prefixes, expiration dates, and so on.

You can use the census uploader to:

* Add a New Group Account Census
* Populate a Group Benefits Census with Data

Modifying The Census Table

You can modify member data in the census table by clicking in the field and modifying the data. Changes are saved by clicking Next. Members can be deleted by clicking the trash can icon next to their name.

It's a good idea to create and upload a new member census file when there's significant changes to the number of members in a group and for different quotes or annual renewals.

The Census Record Page

You'll see the following on the Census Upload tab:

* A table with member data
* An Add Employee button at the top of the table
* An Add User icon on the action column of each row
* A trash can icon to delete members

You must activate the record page as the default record page in order for the census uploader to work.

You can use the Census Uploader to:

* Add a new group benefits census to a group account
* Populate a Group Benefits Census with Data
title: Uploading Group Benefits Census with Vlocity
